derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: from Old French dozeine, based on Latin duodecim 'twelve'

encyclopedia.content: ['d∧zn] adj n. dozen或dozens<缩写为doz> 一打 12个 dozens of 许多、很多

entry.def: If you have a dozen things, you have twelve of them.

example.ex: You will be able to take ten dozen bottles free of duty through customs...
example.tran: 你可以携带120瓶免税通过海关。

entry.def: You can refer to a group of approximately twelve things or people as a dozen. You can refer to a group of approximately six things or people as half a dozen .

example.ex: I was sitting only a dozen feet away...
example.tran: 我正坐在只有十几英尺远的地方。

example.ex: In half a dozen words, he had explained the bond that linked them...
example.tran: 他用了六七个字就解释清楚了他们之间的关系。

entry.def: If you refer to dozens of things or people, you are emphasizing that there are very many of them.

example.ex: ...a storm which destroyed dozens of homes and buildings.
example.tran: 摧毁了许多房屋和建筑的暴风雨

means.word_mean: 1. the cardinal number that is the sum of eleven and one
1. denoting a quantity consisting of 12 items or units
